# ClaudeTask Framework Environment Configuration

# MongoDB Atlas Configuration (Optional - for cloud storage)
# To use MongoDB Atlas instead of local SQLite:
# 1. Create a MongoDB Atlas account at https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas
# 2. Create a cluster (M0 Free Tier recommended for testing)
# 3. Get connection string from Atlas UI
# 4. Create Voyage AI account at https://www.voyageai.com/
# 5. Get API key from Voyage AI dashboard

# MongoDB connection string (format: mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/)
# MONGODB_CONNECTION_STRING=mongodb+srv://user:password@cluster.mongodb.net/?retryWrites=true&w=majority

# MongoDB database name (default: claudetask)
# MONGODB_DATABASE_NAME=claudetask

# Voyage AI API key (format: vo-...)
# Required for voyage-3-large embeddings (1024 dimensions)
# VOYAGE_AI_API_KEY=vo-your-api-key-here

# Note: Leave these commented out to use local storage (SQLite + ChromaDB) by default
